The paper discusses the use of text classifiers in causal inference, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of established modeling mechanisms from the causality literature on missing data and measurement error, which falls under the category of statistics and data analysis. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CY (Computers and Society), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are also likely sub-categories.
